/*Instructions for the animations:
*If you want a specific part of the rotating hues to be gone, comment the one animation: huerotate line and it will stop. What I mean by comment is putting the one line into these forward slash asterisk tags.
*If you want all of the animations to be gone, simply comment the @keyframes line down below. Every one of the animations will be gone, you don't have to comment any other lines.
*If you need any help with it, feel free to PM Supernova283! 
*/
 
@keyframes huerotate {
    0% {filter: hue-rotate(0deg);}
    25% {filter: hue-rotate(90deg);}
    50% {filter: hue-rotate(180deg);}
    75% {filter: hue-rotate(270deg);}
    100% {filter: hue-rotate(360deg);}
}
 
div#content, h1, div#page-wrapper {
    animation: huerotate 4s infinite;
}
 
